# advertising-creative / HTMLCSStoImage

Render deterministic, version-controllable HTML + CSS into a high-quality PNG/JPG/WebP
ad creative via the hosted HCTI API (Chrome rendering engine). You author the markup;
the cloud renders the pixels. Note: this is a SaaS, not a local headless renderer — it
needs HCTI credentials and a network round-trip.

controls do
  advertising-creative.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  advertising-creative.html: { label: "HTML fragment", type: "textarea" }
  advertising-creative.css: { label: "CSS", type: "textarea" }
  advertising-creative.format: { label: "Output format", type: "select", options: ["png", "jpg", "webp", "pdf"] }
end

## Required reading

- HCTI API docs (official, proprietary): https://docs.htmlcsstoimage.com/
- HCTI MCP server (official): https://docs.htmlcsstoimage.com/integrations/mcp/
  — `claude mcp add hcti --transport http https://mcp.hcti.io`
- Docs source repo: https://github.com/htmlcsstoimage/docs
- Community curl examples (unverified license, reference only): https://docs.htmlcsstoimage.com/integrations/

## Render

```bash
# Requires an hcti.io account (free tier 50 imgs/mo). Network call, NOT local.
export HCTI_USER=... HCTI_KEY=...   # from hcti.io dashboard

ID=$(curl -s -X POST https://hcti.io/v1/image -u "$HCTI_USER:$HCTI_KEY" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"html":"<div class=card>OOTA</div>","css":".card{font-family:sans-serif;font-size:48px;padding:40px;background:#111;color:#fff}"}' \
  | python3 -c 'import sys,json;print(json.load(sys.stdin)["id"])')

curl -s "https://hcti.io/v1/image/$ID.png" -o out/creative.png
file out/creative.png   # expect: PNG image data
```

## Failure modes

- **Not local/headless:** rendering happens on hcti.io servers. No credentials or no
  network means no render — the step writes source only and degrades gracefully.
- **Free-tier cap:** 50 images/mo; over the cap returns a billing/rate error, not an image.
- **Auth:** uses HTTP Basic `USER_ID:API_KEY` (not a bearer token); wrong order or missing
  key returns 401/403.
- **Nondeterministic pixels:** pin `google_fonts`, `viewport_width`/`viewport_height`, and
  `device_scale` or output drifts between renders.
- **CDN URL, not a file:** the POST returns `.url`/`.id`; you must GET `{id}.png` (or `.jpg`/
  `.webp`/`.pdf`) to materialize a local file.
- **Determinism boundary:** if OOTA needs fully-local deterministic image-from-markup, use
  Chromium/Playwright or wkhtmltoimage instead of HCTI.
